      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 27 Parenting column about seventh-grade handwriting champion at St Pius V Catholic School in Melville, NY (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Parenting column last Sunday, about a seventh-grade handwriting champion at a Roman Catholic school, St. Pius V, in Melville, gave an incomplete account of the circumstances surrounding the suspensions of several students last year. While a parent said the suspensions were for remarks about the school's nuns that students posted on the Internet, the principal, Sister Maria Dolorosa, said the students were suspended because they used the Internet to view movies and listen to music that they knew were prohibited by the school.</p>
      </block>
